<TITLE> Power, energy get 61.5pc rise </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 10 (bdnews24.com)--Staying true to his pre-budget speech, the finance minister has proposed a whopping 61.5 percent hike in power and energy over the revised budget of the outgoing fiscal year. AMA Muhith in his budget announcement on Thursday proposed allocation Tk 61.15 billion in energy and power for the 2010-11 fiscal year, which is 61.5 percent higher than the revised budget. He earlier said the budget proposal will focus on resolving power and energy crises
